Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}(minced). Zest the
@lemon{1} and @orange{1} (you'll need about ½ teaspoon from each). Peel the
orange with your hands before thinly slicing, end to end, into rounds. Remove
any seeds. Halve the lemon. Thinly slice the @celery{1}(thinly sliced).

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together the juice of half a lemon, 2 Tablespoons
shallot, the lemon and orange zest, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{4%teaspoon}
(to taste). Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Set half the
dressing aside for the couscous.

== Couscous ==

Cook the couscous: Bring 1 cup water and a pinch of salt to a boil in a
#small pot{}. Once boiling, add the @couscous{1/2%cup}. Cover and remove from
heat.

== Salmon ==

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat dry the
@skin-on salmon{12%ounce} with a #paper towel{}. Season on all sides with salt,
pepper, and the @Turkish spice blend{1%tablespoon}. Add the salmon to the pan.
Cook ~{3-4%minutes} per side, until opaque in the middle. Remove and discard the
skin.

== Salad ==

Toss the @arugula{2%ounce}, orange, and celery into the #bowl{} with the
dressing. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Add extra olive oil and lemon juice if needed.

== Assembly ==

Finish and serve: Fluff the couscous with a #fork{}, and drizzle with the
reserved lemon shallot dressing. Serve the spiced salmon on a bed of couscous
with the orange arugula salad on the side. Enjoy!